@startuml RemoteWorkerWarmupSequence
title Remote Login and Navigation Sequence (Worker-Only Login)

actor User
participant "CFVCore/CFVMain\n(UI process)" as UI
participant "Remote Config\nDialog" as Config
participant "Login Progress\nDialog" as Login
participant "Remote Navigator\nDialog" as Nav
participant "QProcess\nstdin/stdout pipe" as Pipe
participant "cf-worker\n(worker process)" as Worker
participant "Worker Remote\nSession Pool" as Pool

== Select Remote Configuration ==
User -> UI : Open Remote...
UI -> Config : show()
User -> Config : choose protocol/auth + Save
Config --> UI : configuration descriptor

== Worker Login (single connection) ==
UI -> Login : show() [non-modal, log dialog]
UI -> Pipe : #TASK_KIND:REMOTE_PREPARE
UI -> Pipe : #TASK_PAYLOAD_B64:{session_id, descriptor_hash, descriptor}
note right of UI
  CFVMain._pending_prepare_loop\n(QEventLoop) spins here
end note
Pipe -> Worker : parse task
Worker -> Pool : prepare(descriptor_hash, descriptor)
Pool --> Worker : connecting
Worker -> Pipe : REMOTE_STATUS {phase=preparing, message=...}
Pipe -> UI : forward message to Login dialog
Worker -> Pipe : REMOTE_STATUS {phase=ready,...}
Pipe -> UI : quit QEventLoop; close Login dialog

== User Navigates via IPC ==
UI -> Nav : open navigator (no UI-side filesystem connection)
User -> Nav : expand tree node

loop for each directory expansion
  Nav -> UI : list_callback(path) [nested QEventLoop]
  UI -> Pipe : #TASK_KIND:REMOTE_LIST
  UI -> Pipe : #TASK_PAYLOAD_B64:{session_id, descriptor_hash, descriptor, path}
  Pipe -> Worker : parse task
  Worker -> Pool : get(descriptor_hash) [reuse warm session]
  Pool --> Worker : ready session
  Worker -> Worker : fs.ls(path) + normalize + resolve links
  Worker -> Pipe : REMOTE_LIST_RESULT {path, entries[], error}
  Pipe -> UI : quit nested QEventLoop
  UI -> Nav : return list[RemoteEntry]
  Nav -> Nav : populate tree node
end

== Open Selected Remote URI ==
User -> Nav : select file + Open
Nav --> UI : selected_uri + selected_path
UI -> Pipe : #TASK_KIND:REMOTE_OPEN
UI -> Pipe : #TASK_PAYLOAD_B64:{session_id, descriptor_hash, descriptor, uri, path}
Pipe -> Worker : parse task
Worker -> Pool : get(descriptor_hash) [reuse warm session]
Pool --> Worker : session (guaranteed warm from navigation)
Worker -> Worker : open/read metadata for uri
Worker -> Pipe : METADATA {field list payload}
Pipe -> UI : populate field list
Worker -> Pipe : REMOTE_OPEN_RESULT {ok=true, uri=...}
Pipe -> UI : open result

== Target Change / Cleanup ==
User -> UI : choose a different remote target
UI -> Pipe : #TASK_KIND:REMOTE_RELEASE
UI -> Pipe : #TASK_PAYLOAD_B64:{session_id, descriptor_hash}
Pipe -> Worker : parse task
Worker -> Pool : release/evict matching entry
Worker -> Pipe : REMOTE_STATUS {phase=released,...}
Pipe -> UI : status line

note right of Pool
Implemented pool policy:
- Key by descriptor_hash
- TTL idle eviction
- LRU cap
- Most-recent session_id wins
end note

@enduml
